2. Commercial License (REQUIRES PERMISSION)

For commercial use, you must obtain explicit written permission from the copyright owner by contacting: [vixshan@gmail.com](mailto:vixshan@gmail.com)

a) What Requires a Commercial License

You need a commercial license if you intend to:

- Offer Amina as a service (hosting, managed instances, SaaS)
- Integrate Amina into a commercial product
- Charge fees for using Amina or derivative works
- Distribute Amina as part of a commercial offering
- Use Amina for internal business operations that generate profit
- Sublicense Amina to other commercial entities

b) Commercial License Terms

Commercial licenses are negotiated on a case-by-case basis and may include:

- Custom service level agreements
- Commercial support
- Indemnification clauses
- Custom patent licensing terms
- Revenue sharing arrangements (if applicable)

Contact the copyright owner to discuss commercial licensing options.

