How This Works in Practice

Example 1: Personal Use ✅ FREE
You want to modify Amina for your personal Discord server. You can do this under the Non-Commercial License at no cost. Simply include the license file and attribution (as long as you do not gain any profit, even through modules like premium features).

Example 2: Open-Source Contribution ✅ FREE
You want to contribute improvements to Amina that will be merged back into the main project. This is free under the Non-Commercial License since it's for non-commercial purposes.

Example 3: Hosting Service ❌ REQUIRES COMMERCIAL LICENSE
You want to offer "Amina as a Service" where users pay you to host and manage Amina instances. This requires a Commercial License. Contact the copyright owner to negotiate terms.

Example 4: Discord Bot Marketplace ❌ REQUIRES COMMERCIAL LICENSE
You want to sell Amina or a heavily modified version on a Discord bot marketplace. This requires a Commercial License negotiation.

Example 5: Internal Company Use ⚖️ DEPENDS
You want to use Amina internally at your company for operational purposes that doesn't generate direct revenue. This is likely covered under Non-Commercial. If Amina directly contributes to revenue generation (e.g., it's core to your SaaS offering), you need a Commercial License.

